entry.title: Rising Food Prices Roil Developing World
entry.content: Soaring prices are triggering shortages and protests as disruption from the Ukraine war adds to existing strains on global supplies of grains, meat and other foodstuffs.

entry.title: How Putin Drove Finland Into NATO's Arms
entry.content: For many Finns, Russia’s assault on Ukraine recalled the 1939 Soviet invasion of their homeland. Fear of another attack was enough to dismantle Helsinki’s seven-decade strategy of heavily armed nonalignment. “We have no other option.”
